-- RWE Sells Third U.K. Wind Power Project to Germany’s Renerco
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2011-12-27T17:28:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/rwe-sells-third-u-k-wind-power-project-to-germany-s-renerco.html
RWE AG  sold a 20-megawatt wind power
project to  Renerco Renewable Energy Concepts AG (8RN)  as part of a
deal enabling the German developer to buy as many as 10 RWE wind
farms in  England ,  Scotland  and Wales.  The “Cotton Farm” near Cambridgeshire is the third
project Renerco has purchased from RWE’s Npower Renewables unit
as part of a framework agreement reached last year, Munich-based
Renerco said in a  statement  posted on its website today. No
terms were given. Construction is to start in May, according to
the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
